{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nEnabling `identity.require_authenticated` must break nothing on the Gerrit side. Not every\nGerrit-side service writes **in-scope** ticket events, so this story **classifies** them\n(with file/line evidence) rather than blanket-signing everything, and confirms the one in-scope\nwriter actually signs on the deployed VM (finishing canary 1787, which was force-closed\n\"pending post-deploy run\").\n\n## What — enumerate and classify every Gerrit-side store operation\n\nClassification (verified against the code):\n\n- **opcert-service → NON-WRITING.** `src/rebar/opcert_service/jobs.py:11-12` (\"The server never\n  pushes… runs with `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off`\"), enforced at `jobs.py:196-208` (`_sync_push_off`),\n  workspace discarded `jobs.py:97-99`; `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:168-169`\n  (\"STORE-READ-ONLY\" / `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH: \"off\"`). Never places an event on the shared store.\n- **review-bot `code_review` artifact → GATE-EXEMPT.** `src/rebar/review_bot/voter.py:241-251`\n  (`create_ticket(\"code_review\", …)`) + `llm/code_review/sidecar.py:26,143`\n  (`REVIEW_RESULT`); `code_review ∈ _GATE_EXEMPT_TYPES` at\n  `src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py:125`.\n- **review-bot reciprocal `relates_to` LINK on the trailer-cited work ticket → IN-SCOPE\n  WRITER.** `voter.py:278` `rebar.link(artifact_id, resolved, \"relates_to\")` where `resolved`\n  is a real work ticket; `graph/_links.py:264-267` writes a reciprocal LINK event into the\n  work-ticket dir → `_seam.append_event(work_ticket, \"LINK\", …)`; pushed\n  (`docker-compose.yml:93` `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH: \"always\"`). The work ticket is non-exempt, so the\n  gate collects this LINK event. Its on-box backfill reconciler (`review_bot/reconcile.py:223`,\n  launched `app.py:101`) drives the same voter.\n- **auto-lander → RETIRED** (ADR-0047; `infra/gerrit/project.config:53`), not deployed.\n- (For contrast: the Jira→rebar reconciler is a GitHub-side writer — `reconcile-bridge.yml`,\n  `runs-on: ubuntu-latest` — covered by story 4dc0, NOT Gerrit-side.)\n\n**Already provisioned to sign:** `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh:98-124` materializes SSM\n`/rebar/prod/rebar-bot-signing-key` to a `0600` file and exports `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`;\nthe write seam (`_seam.py:294-315`) signs when a resolvable `author_id` (594c, via the bot git\nemail) + a `signing_key` are present. So the review-bot is equipped to sign its LINK writes as\nidentity `594c`.\n\n## Confirming canary 1787 (the in-scope path signs on the deployed VM)\n\nThe in-scope writer is exercised naturally by pushing a change through Gerrit: the deployed\nreview-bot reviews the change and emits a reciprocal `relates_to` LINK onto the change's\n`rebar-ticket:` work ticket, authored by `594c`. Confirm that LINK event is **signed +\nverified** — that is the deployed-VM proof. (Fallback: inspect the running review-bot container\non the VM via AWS SSM to confirm the key is materialized and `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY` is\nset.)\n\n## Scope\n\nGerrit-side operations only: classification + verification. Provisioning only if an in-scope\nwriter is found **unsigned** (it is already provisioned). No enforcement flip here (8d39). No\ntracked repo-file change (empty `file_impact` is correct); the classification + canary evidence\nare recorded as comments on this ticket.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] **Every Gerrit-side store operation is enumerated and classified** non-writing /\n      gate-exempt / in-scope-writer, with file/line evidence, recorded on this ticket (the\n      table above).\n- [ ] **The in-scope Gerrit-side writer produces a signed, verified event.** A review-bot\n      reciprocal `relates_to` LINK on a work ticket `<t>`, authored by `594c`, verifies. Proving\n      evidence: `rebar show <t> | jq -e '.authorship.signed >= 1'` (signature present on the\n      LINK-target ticket), and the LINK event **verifies** — record its event uuid `E` and\n      assert its **absence** from the non-verified report (verified events are excluded —\n      `verify_authorship.py:503-504`):\n      `rebar verify-identity --all --format json | jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'`\n      exits 0. The LINK event uuid `E` is recorded on this ticket.\n- [ ] **Confirmed unaffected by enforcement:** the opcert-service (`REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off`, never\n      pushes) and the review-bot `code_review` artifacts (gate-exempt) are not rejected when\n      `require_authenticated=true` — established by the classification evidence above.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] Canary 1787 is re-run for the in-scope path on the deployed VM (or an\n      equivalent live Gerrit change that drives the review-bot). Evidence recorded on this\n      ticket: the signed LINK event id + its `verified` verdict (or the SSM/container inspection\n      showing the materialized key), with a timestamp."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784235944563739001,"uuid":"3d856efe-3daf-4e73-8b2c-17b5b76b4050"}